{#-
  General Home Mobile — theme macro library.
  Deployed to custom_templates/general_home_theme.jinja by the sync script.

  Card-mod styles in dashboard.yaml import these macros and render CSS for
  the viewer: `user` (injected by card-mod, equals the account's display
  name) picks whose helpers to read, and that account's Theme Mode select
  (Light/Dark/System) picks which palette variant renders. System emits
  both variants under prefers-color-scheme media queries so the device
  decides; a fixed mode emits one plain block and the device setting is
  ignored. Any session that is not <entity_31> falls back to <entity_32>'s
  theme (shared devices, guests).

  Only card_mod `style:` templates receive `user`. Other template contexts
  (auto-entities filters, mushroom secondaries, markdown content) must pass
  the account name as a literal argument instead.

  Tables:
    palette_colors   — semantic accent colors, identical in both modes
    palette_by_mode  — glows / page surface / glass background, per mode
    style_by_mode    — card chrome + background fallbacks, per style per mode
    style_blur       — blur defaults, per style (same in both modes)
-#}

